Diagnosis.
Metallic green (
Fig. 30–31
), deep blue-green (
Fig. 29
), dark blue (
Fig. 54
), green-yellow or red. Sides of pronotal disc finely granulate (
Figs 29, 31
, 
54
). Pronotal disc coarsely granulorugose (
Figs 29, 31
, 
54
). Posteromedial process of pronotum produced into triangular denticle, widened laterally, not bifurcated apically (
Figs 42
, 
54
). Anteromedial portion of pronotal disc with two strongly developed denticles (
Fig. 54
). Anterolateral margins of pronotal disc with inconspicuous line of tubercles (
Fig. 54
). Posterolateral angles of pronotum more developed than posteromedial process (
Figs 42
, 
54
). Elytral striae scabriculous, coarsely impressed, coarsely punctate (
Figs 29–31
). Elytral interstriae highly vermiculate, superficially punctate, convex (
Figs 29–31
).
